      "content": "The state must draw a hard line where religious freedom cannot be used as a shield to deny basic human rights or safety to others, as no belief system justifies harming vulnerable people. While we must protect religious liberty, it is not absolute when it conflicts with the fundamental rights of the public, such as access to healthcare or protection from discrimination. A functional society requires that the government enforce necessary mandates to ensure public safety and equality, even if it means limiting certain religious exemptions that would otherwise cause direct harm.",
